source: This tutorial will walk you through how to use the pretrained models for generating plots from the boiling image data. For this tutorial you will need to download and unzip steady state test data [here](https://osf.io/2gwj5). Or you can use your own boiling data if you have both the video in .avi format and the frames saved as .jpgs. You will also need to download the saved model weights [here](https://osf.io/uy2ad).

# Define the parameters for the model:
imagesfolder="./Images-120W"   # Define the path to the folder of images
videopath="./120W.avi"    # Define the path to the avi video
savefolder="./SaveData/"   # Define the folder you want the data to save in
extension="Test1"    # Define the extension you want all the saved data to have. This should be unique for each experiment
thres=0.5    # Define the threshold for what the model identifies as a bubble
modelweights="./model_final.pth"     # Define the path to the saved model weights.
device='cpu'   # Specify if running on "cpu" or "gpu"
